Pre-Game Insights: Jesse Winker said the Mets have fought all year, and they need to keep their head down and keep going, keep plugging away at it.
This team has fought all year, so to be in this position isn’t really new to us,
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Mets deployed both Ryne Stanek and closer Edwin Díaz for multiple innings in Game 5, knowing it was a must-win game with an off-day to follow.
The Dodgers will be in significantly better shape for Game 6 after Brent Honeywell spared the bulk of his bullpen by gobbling up 14 outs.
Freddie Freeman has struggled at the plate as he continues to nurse a badly sprained right ankle, and he was held out of the starting lineup for Game 6.
The Mets became the first team since the 2022 Angels to avoid striking out in a postseason game.
It has happened 11 times in the playoffs.
Others: The game will be played at Dodger Stadium on Sunday, with first pitch scheduled for 8:08 p.m. ET/5:08 p.m. PT on FS1.
The Mets will go with the same lineup that they used in the Mets' 12-6 Game 5 win, including Jeff McNeil at second base.
The Dodgers will go with a bullpen game on Sunday, with Michael Kopech taking the ball to start the game.
